US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson pressed allies to meet a defence spending goal of 2% of GDP, urging each country to have a plan in place to fulfil funding commitments to Nato. WASHINGTON - US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson, in his first North Atlantic Treaty Organisation (Nato) meeting in Brussels, told allies that the United States will uphold previous agreements and ensure the alliance has the capability to defend itself, including from Russian aggression.He also pressed allies to meet a defence spending goal of 2% of gross domestic product, urging each country to either meet or have a plan in place to fulfil funding commitments to Nato by a May summit of Nato leaders.